%% seq_04_review.mmd
%% Scope: Review lifecycle (auto-create → submit → confirm → scores)
%% Backend refs:
%%   - trigger_listeners.ts → task:status:changed (newStatus='done')
%%   - POST /reviews/:id/submit → SubmitReviewController → SubmitSkillReviewCommand
%%   - POST /reviews/:id/confirm → ConfirmReviewController → ConfirmReviewCommand
%%   - POST /reviews/:id/reverse → SubmitReverseReviewController
%%   - GET /reviews/:id → ShowReviewController
%%   - POST /api/reviews/sessions → CreateReviewSessionController (manual)
%%   - DetectAnomalyCommand (async via review:submitted event)
%%   - ⚠️ Reviews are PARALLEL (manager + peers, no ordering)
%%   - ⚠️ No invite-peers route exists
%%   - ⚠️ Score commands NOT auto-triggered
%%   - ⚠️ Transmit transport=null (no WebSocket)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Sys as System (Event Listener)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    actor Mgr as Manager
    actor Peer as Peer Reviewer
    actor Rev as Reviewee
    participant B as Browser (Svelte)
    participant Cmd as Command

    Note over Sys, Cmd: === TASK → DONE: AUTO-CREATE REVIEW SESSION ===

    Sys->>Sys: Event 'task:status:changed'
    (newStatus === 'done')
    Sys->>DB: Find active assignments for task
    DB-->>Sys: Assignment(s)

    loop For each active assignment
        Sys->>DB: UPDATE assignment
        SET status = 'completed'
        Sys->>DB: INSERT INTO review_sessions
        (task_assignment_id, reviewee_id,
        status='pending',
        required_peer_reviews=2,
        deadline=NOW()+14 days)
    end

    Note over Sys, Cmd: === SUBMIT REVIEW (PARALLEL) ===
    Note over Mgr, Peer: Manager and peers can submit
    Note over Mgr, Peer: independently, in ANY order

    Mgr->>B: Open review
    B->>Cmd: GET /reviews/:id
    Cmd-->>B: Session + skills to review

    Mgr->>B: Rate each skill (level + comment)
    B->>Cmd: POST /reviews/:id/submit
    Note over Cmd: SubmitSkillReviewCommand

    Cmd->>DB: INSERT INTO skill_reviews
    (reviewer_type='manager',
    assigned_level_code, comment)
    Cmd->>DB: UPDATE review_sessions
    SET manager_review_completed = TRUE
    Cmd->>Cmd: determineSessionStatus()
    Note over Cmd: pending → in_progress
    Note over Cmd: (on first submission)
    Cmd->>Sys: emit('review:submitted')

    Note over Sys: Async: DetectAnomalyCommand
    Note over Sys: checks 3/6 patterns:
    Note over Sys: bulk_same_level,
    Note over Sys: new_account_high, mutual_high

    par Peer reviews (parallel)
        Peer->>B: Rate skills
        B->>Cmd: POST /reviews/:id/submit
        Cmd->>DB: INSERT INTO skill_reviews
        (reviewer_type='peer')
        Cmd->>DB: peer_reviews_count += 1
        Cmd->>Cmd: determineSessionStatus()
    end

    Note over Cmd: When managerReviewCompleted
    Note over Cmd: && peerReviewsCount >= required:
    Note over Cmd: status → 'completed' (auto)

    Note over Sys, Cmd: === REVIEWEE CONFIRM / DISPUTE ===
    Note over Cmd: ConfirmReviewCommand
    Note over Cmd: REQUIRES status = 'completed'

    Rev->>B: View completed review
    B->>Cmd: GET /reviews/:id
    Cmd-->>B: spider chart + skill levels

    alt Agree
        Rev->>B: Click "Confirm"
        B->>Cmd: POST /reviews/:id/confirm
        (body: { action: 'confirmed' })
        Cmd->>DB: UPDATE confirmations JSONB
        Cmd->>Sys: emit('review:confirmed')
        Note over Sys: Updates credibility_data
    else Dispute
        Rev->>B: Click "Dispute" + reason
        B->>Cmd: POST /reviews/:id/confirm
        (body: { action: 'disputed', reason })
        Cmd->>DB: UPDATE confirmations JSONB
        Cmd->>DB: SET status = 'disputed'
    end

    Note over Sys, Cmd: === REVERSE REVIEW ===

    Rev->>B: Rate reviewers
    B->>Cmd: POST /reviews/:id/reverse
    Cmd->>DB: INSERT INTO reverse_reviews
    (target_type, target_id, rating,
    comment, is_anonymous)
    Cmd-->>B: Saved

    Note over Sys, Cmd: === SCORE CALCULATION ===

    Note over Sys, Cmd: === TIMEOUT MECHANISM ===
    Note over Sys: Scheduler runs periodically:
    Note over Sys: CloseExpiredReviewSessionsCommand
    alt Review deadline exceeded
        Sys->>DB: SELECT review_sessions
        WHERE status IN ('pending','in_progress')
        AND deadline < NOW()
        DB-->>Sys: Expired sessions
        Sys->>DB: UPDATE review_sessions
        SET status = 'completed'
        (force-close with available reviews)
        Sys->>Sys: emit('review:force_closed')
    end

    Note over Sys, Cmd: === LATE TASK CHECK ===
    alt Task completed after due_date
        Cmd->>DB: SELECT completed_at, due_date
        FROM task_assignments JOIN tasks
        DB-->>Cmd: Dates comparison
        Note over Cmd: Mark as late submission
        Note over Cmd: Late penalty applied to scores (TBD)
    end

    Note over Cmd: ⚠️ NOT auto-triggered
    Note over Cmd: Must be called explicitly:
    Note over Cmd: CalculateSpiderChartCommand
    Note over Cmd: CalculateTrustScoreCommand

    opt Reviewee is freelancer
        Calc->>DB: UPDATE users
        SET freelancer_rating = new_rating,
        freelancer_completed_tasks_count += 1
        WHERE id = reviewee_id
        DB-->>Calc: Freelancer rating updated
    end

    Calc->>DB: UPDATE review_sessions
    SET status = 'completed',
    completed_at = NOW()
    DB-->>Calc: Session finalized

    Sys->>WS: Notify all: "Review completed"


